      • equalsByValue

        public boolean equalsByValue(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks for equality amongst other Unsigned types. This allows equality checks between UnsignedWord and either UnsignedByte and UnsignedShort. Essentially, UnsignedWord.valueOf(0).equalsByValue(UnsignedByte.valueOf(0)) == true;
        Parameters:
        obj - The object to compare to.
        Returns:
        True if the objects values are the same
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - Obj cannot be cast to an UnsignedByte, UnsignedShort, or UnsignedWord.
